2010-07-08  Don McCoy  <don@codesourcery.com>

	* src/vsip/opt/reductions/reductions.hpp: Added evaluator name()
	  overload for diagnostic purposes.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/reductions.cpp: Added reduction functions to
	  handle matrices by-row.  Got rid of partial_sumsq() by adding a
	  boolean parameter to partial_sum().  Added support for meansq.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/reductions.hpp: Added 'meansq' to list of 
	  supported reduction types.  Added new evaluator for matrix reductions.
	  Spelled out the reduction template parameter name in the evaluators.
	  Added meta-function for extracting real values from either real or
   	  complex inputs.  Added traits classes to support thresholding.
	  Commented compile-time and run-time checks in evaluators.
	  Fixed a run-time check preventing dispatch when the result type
	  doesn't match the input block's value type (i.e. the mag-squared
	  cases involving complex inputs).
	* benchmarks/meansqval.cpp: Corrected ops_per_point() so that it
	  accounted for the number of rows per "point".  Corrected validation
	  check.  Added diag() function for matrix reduction case.  Added
	  complex float case.

