2009-11-02  Mike LeBlanc  <mike@codesourcery.com>

	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/binary_params.h: Add ATAN2.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/unary_params.h: Add ATAN, COS, ZCOS, SIN, ZSIN.

	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/assign.hpp: Enable dispatch for ATAN, COS,
	    ZCOS, SIN, ZSIN and ATAN2.

	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/unary.hpp: Declare vatan(), vcos() and vsin().
	    Note these are supported as plugins.  Define their thresholds.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/unary.cpp: Define those functions to load and
	    invoke the appropriate plugins.

	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/binary.hpp: Declare vatan2() and set its
	    threshold.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/ppu/binary.cpp: Define vatan2() to load and invoke
	    the appropriate plugin.  Also, there is code, now commented out,
	    to load and invoke the plugin for complex divide.  Enable it when
	    the plugin is more precise.

	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/spu/plugin/unary_f.c: Add plugins for ATAN, COS,
	    ZCOS, SIN, ZSIN.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/spu/plugin/xvdiv_f.c: Add a plugin for complex
	    divide.  It does not produce results precise enough, but this
	    plugin is disabled for now.
	* src/vsip/opt/cbe/spu/plugin/binary_f.c: New file.  Put new binary
	    plugins here.  ATAN2 is the first.

	* benchmarks/expr/vatan.cpp: New file.  Benchmarks for vatan() and
	    vatan2().
	* benchmarks/expr/vcos.cpp: New file.  Benchmarks for vsin() and
	    vcos().
	* benchmarks/sumval.cpp: Add benchmarks for sumval() complex<float>.

