2009-05-29  Don McCoy  <don@codesourcery.com>

	* benchmarks/fastconv.cpp: Reverted unintentional changes from previous
	  patch.

2009-05-28  Don McCoy  <don@codesourcery.com>

	* src/vsip/core/fft/backend.hpp (supports_cuda_memory()): Added
	  new virtual function indicating whether or not a backend understands
	  how to utilize "device memory" resident on GPU cards.
	* src/vsip/opt/fft/workspace.hpp: Modified to extract pointers to GPU
	  memory instead of host memory, if the CUDA backend is enabled.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/bindings.hpp: Utilize size() instead of impl_stride()
	  in memory copy functions for compatibility with expression blocks.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/kernels.hpp (smmul_ss, smmul_sc): Added  declarations
	  for scalar-matrix elementwise multiply.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/gpu_block.hpp: Corrected device_flush() to copy
	  data the correct direction.  Added impl_data() override so that
	  data is copied back to the host for users of Ext_data.  Removed 
	  commented-out code.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/eval_vmmul.hpp: Corrected comment.  Added 
	  parenthesis in conditional to avoid warning.  Modified the sync
	  parameter for the output block to avoid a possible redundant copy.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/fft.cpp: Added scaling capability.  Removed calls
	  to push memory back and forth as this is now handled either by 
	  Gpu_block or Device_memory.  Override the name() member function
	  where not done previously.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/kernels/vmmul.cu: Implemented scalar-matrix 
	  multiply kernels for scalar and complex-interleaved matrices.
	* src/vsip/opt/cuda/device_memory.hpp: Added code to aid in debugging.
	  Taught non-gpu-block versions to use the run-time ext data class 
	  Rt_ext_data.  This effectively provides support for blocks containing
	  complex-split data by creating an interleaved copy.
	* benchmarks/cuda/vmmul.cpp: Fixed order of includes such that CUDA
	  headers are seen before our definitions are seen.
	* benchmarks/cuda/fftm.cpp: Likewise.

2009-05-28  Stefan Seefeld <stefan@codesourcery.com>

	* src/vsip_csl/expr/functor.hpp: new ReturnFunctor templates.
	* src/vsip_csl/expr/eval.hpp: Support for custom expression evaluation.

